---
title: Very Teriyaki Pork Tenderloin with Basmati Rice and Asparagus
description: Forget the bottled stuff—making your own teriyaki sauce is a cinch. All you need is a glug of soy sauce plus a good pinch of something sweet, and you’re in business. And with this simple, Japanese-style stir-fry recipe under your belt, it’s easy to make any time teriyaki time. Here, we’re using pork tenderloin and asparagus, but the sauce works well with a wide variety of proteins and veg.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w19-r7-a70b7a2f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w19-r7-9a652f49.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  saturated fat: 2.5 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 520 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/very-teriyaki-pork-tenderloin-58d3c72f2310a86c324929c3
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Fill 2 medium #pots{} with @water{2 1/2%cups} and a
@salt{pinch} each and bring to a boil. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Peel
and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and discard bottom inch from
@asparagus{12%ounce}, then cut into 2-inch pieces. Trim, then thinly slice
@scallions{4%unit}, keeping greens and whites separate. Fill a #large bowl{}
with ice water.

Once water is boiling, add @Basmati rice{1 1/2%cup} to one of the #pots{}. Cover,
lower heat, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove
from heat and keep covered until meal is ready.

Add asparagus to other pot of water and boil until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Meanwhile, whisk together @soy sauce{4%tablespoon}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon},
and @honey{4%teaspoon} in a #small bowl{}. When asparagus is done, drain and
immediately place in ice water.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Halve @pork tenderloin{24%ounce} lengthwise, then cut into
strips. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Put @cornstarch{2%tablespoon}
in #medium bowl{}, then add pork and toss to coat. Discard any excess
cornstarch. Add pork to pan in a single layer and cook until browned,
~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Tip: Cook pork in batches to avoid overcrowding.

Remove pork from pan and set aside. Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium
heat. Add ginger, scallion whites, and garlic and toss until fragrant, about
~{30%seconds}. Add sauce, asparagus, and pork and toss until cooked through,
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide between plates and top with stir-fry. Sprinkle
with scallion greens and serve.